<BR>
<font size="1">"One man plus the truth equals a majority."<BR>
Cerivel tells you, 'Hehe grats on scaring off a level 56 giant that hits for 360'<BR><BR>
Paladin of the 49th shield<BR>
<a href="http://www.emeraldis.com/~booraembj/">Exiles</a>, Xegony<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 887<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 9:07:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=308.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1hs vs, 2hs, the eternal debate...</span><hr size=1> I don't have a specific number, but 1 handers are maybe doing 70%ish the damage of a 2 hander. when you talk about relatively equivalent weapons in level and ability to aquire them.<br>
<br>
I would say the problem is with the shields. We shouldn't be doing more damage with a 1 hander. But we should be getting enough of a benefit from wielding a shield and 1 hander that the option is quite reasonable.<br>
<br>
The ac on shields are extremely poor for the loss in damage output you are sacrificing. There isn't a great variety of shields really and there isn't anything over the top of some stat increases (which are not near sufficient to offset the damage loss) and bash (situationally valuable, but normally stuns are sufficient) to make them desirable. <br>
<br>
I would really like to see shields with 100+ ac on them. I would like to see shields with some possible bash proc effects or possibly some great effects like FT3+ or aura of battle or maybe a high +dodge or +parry modifier or something.<br>
Something like this to make the option alot more viable. As it is now, there is a huge disparity between damage output lost from dumping a 2 hander vs damage mitigated from a shield.<br>
<br>
Even though I chew everyone out about using them and I always say they suck, I really do want to use one myself. I like seeing my ac fly up and alot the times when I'm not doing anything productive I'll walk around with whatever shield and 1 hander I've got just to ooogle at my stats. Unfortunately I just can't justify using it as a viable weapon combo with the current state of the game. <br>
<br>
Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1796<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 12:14:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=308.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1hs vs, 2hs, the eternal debate...</span><hr size=1> Just a word on the damage cap pre-20, if you use a high damage weapon before that point and parse it you'll see a lot of hits for max.  I think the engine just takes any hit above 29-31 and uses the 29-31 as your hit.  (Similar to the way min hits on backstabs were implemented, any damage below a point is just moved up to the min)<br>
<br>
My point is 2h pre-20 isn't nearly as bad as it seems ;) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 900<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/28/02 12:42:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=308.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 1hs vs, 2hs, the eternal debate...</span><hr size=1> Yeah, actually I have a little halfling pally twink with a baton of faith 30/40 and seemed to hit consistantly for 20 damage with it.<br>
So you may be right, it might just mitigate the damage down to whatever the cap is in which case alot more hits will be max if it's a big damage weapon.<br>
This even lessens the value of a 1 hander.<br>
